							<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade in active" id="home">
								<h4>Alfa Ship Trading LLC, USA</h4>
								<ulclass="list-style arrow ul-text">
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Established cash buyer operating out of the USA.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Professional expertise, specialization in “as is” tonnage coming out of the Americas and Africa.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Successfully procured almost all tonnage sold by Petrobras, basis “delivery Brazil” and thereafter ballasted and /or towed (Wet & Dry) to the Indian subcontinent.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Over five years ASR and Alfa have together collaborated to trade close to 75 Ships – in tonnage terms - about 535,000 Long Tons LDT.</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="profile">
								<h4>JRD Industries, India</h4>
								<ul class="list-style arrow ul-text">
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> ASR used its expertise to assist in setting up of a model “green” ship recycling facility JRD’s Plot No. 30, Alang</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Amongst the first seven HKC compliant yards certified by Class NK and first two HKC compliant yards certified by Lloyd’s Register (out of the 125 yards operating in India today).</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Standout achievement – awarded the contract to recycle the Royal New Zealand Navy’s tanker - HMNZS Endeavour.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Website: <a href="https://jrdindustries.net/"> www.jrdindustries.net </a></li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="messages">
								<h4>Trinitas Ship Management Pvt Ltd, India</h4>
								<ul class="list-style arrow ul-text">
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Established in 2016.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Team of Masters and Chief Engineers specializing in Single Delivery Voyages (SDV) with an experience of managing over 200 vessels to date.</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Well recognized in the Shipping Market as a quality service provider for management of : <br> 1) Vessels under own power <br> 2) Vessels in cold lay-up requiring reactivation and <br> 3) Dead vessels under tow</li>
									<li> <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Besides complete management of the vessel, Trinitas in addition also assists ASR to make informed decision of the purchase by initiating high quality pre-purchase inspections.</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
